&lt;p&gt;At Flipdish, we’re turning the tables in favour of independent restaurant and takeaway owners by offering powerful, simple-to-use tech solutions backed by real human support. Everything we do is designed to make running a restaurant satisfyingly simple - in a world that’s anything but.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a driven, commercially minded &lt;span class=&quot;notion-enable-hover&quot; data-token-index=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Field Sales Account Executive&lt;/span&gt; to join our fast-growing Sales team. You’ll own your territory’s new business pipeline end-to-end and represent Flipdish in the field, building relationships with restaurant owners, hospitality groups, and franchise operators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on, consultative role that combines pipeline ownership with in-person meetings. You’ll uncover how a venue operates today, diagnose problems and growth opportunities, and help prospective customers modernise how they run operations using Flipdish.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;In this job you’ll:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full sales cycle for your territory - from prospecting and first outreach through discovery, proposals, negotiation, and close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a strong pipeline of qualified opportunities, balancing warm inbound leads with proactive outbound prospecting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run compelling face-to-face meetings and tailored demos that clearly link Flipdish’s value to each customer’s commercial and operational goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Listen, diagnose, and advise - uncover pain points, build a consultative business case, and recommend the right solution and commercial structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate complex deals with multiple stakeholders, handle objections, and move opportunities forward with pace and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Challenge poor decisions and propose better ways of working. Constructive challenge is a responsibility - prioritising harmony over truth or progress is a failure of responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently hit or exceed monthly/quarterly new business targets for your territory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a high-quality, well-forecasted pipeline with clear next steps and strong conversion through each stage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Close deals that are a good fit and onboard smoothly, with low churn risk and clear customer outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll thrive in this role if you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have 2+ years’ experience in sales or business development, ideally in field sales / territory management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a track record of &lt;strong&gt;building your own outbound pipeline&lt;/strong&gt; and consistently hitting or exceeding targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are confident running consultative conversations - asking the right questions, listening well, and connecting product value to business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are highly organised and self-directed - you can plan your territory, manage your time, and follow up without needing constant direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are commercially savvy and comfortable discussing pricing, ROI, and contract terms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The following would help you stand out.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;message-list_1778593937.313929&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Restaurant experience or restaurant tech experience selling SaaS to SMB restaurants&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong negotiation skills and evidence of closing mid-market / multi-site opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with POS, online ordering, loyalty, or restaurant operations tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
